docs.abstract: “I know it’s been a hard day,” Ben Smith, the editor in chief of BuzzFeed News, said in a note to the staff.
docs.snippet: “I know it’s been a hard day,” Ben Smith, the editor in chief of BuzzFeed News, said in a note to the staff.
docs.lead_paragraph: “This is going to be a tough week,” Ben Smith, the editor in chief of BuzzFeed News, wrote in an email to his staff on Wednesday. On Friday, the newsroom learned just how tough, when the company laid off 43 of the roughly 250 journalists who worked in that division, according to a BuzzFeed spokesman.

headline.main: BuzzFeed’s First Round of Layoffs Puts an End to Its National News Desk
headline.print_headline: First Round of BuzzFeed Layoffs Wipes Out a News Desk
